139
00:06:04,427 --> 00:06:07,761
"Hwatch" me.

140
00:06:08,664 --> 00:06:10,064
Fine. I'm sorry.

141
00:06:10,066 --> 00:06:11,932
Thank you for
the thoughtful gift.

142
00:06:11,934 --> 00:06:13,534
I really do appreciate it.

143
00:06:13,536 --> 00:06:17,938
As you know, I had become
attached to my old laptop.

144
00:06:17,940 --> 00:06:19,473
But I'm sure, in time,
that this one will...

145
00:06:19,475 --> 00:06:21,408
(gasps)
Jeepers creepers,

146
00:06:21,410 --> 00:06:23,611
that started up fast!

147
00:06:23,613 --> 00:06:25,646
I thought you might
like it.

148
00:06:25,648 --> 00:06:27,848
Look at the 4K resolution.

149
00:06:27,850 --> 00:06:29,617
Next time we Skype,
I'm gonna count

150
00:06:29,619 --> 00:06:32,620
all those nostril hairs.

151
00:06:32,622 --> 00:06:35,256
Or you could just look
into my eyes.

152
00:06:35,258 --> 00:06:37,358
But you only have two eyes.

153
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:40,494
You got a lot of nostril hairs.

154
00:06:40,496 --> 00:06:42,987
Well, you know,
as long as you're happy.

155
00:06:43,011 --> 00:06:44,533
Oh.

156
00:06:44,534 --> 00:06:46,000
I am. (chuckles)

157
00:06:46,002 --> 00:06:48,636
And Rick said you could bring in
your old one to recycle it.

158
00:06:48,638 --> 00:06:51,539
Oh. Uh, no, no, no, thank you.

159
00:06:51,541 --> 00:06:53,140
Oh, but he said
you can get store credit.

160
00:06:53,142 --> 00:06:55,809
Well, no, I just...
I-I don't want to recycle it.

161
00:06:55,811 --> 00:06:57,411
And I don't want store credit.

162
00:06:57,413 --> 00:06:58,312
But why wouldn't...

163
00:06:58,314 --> 00:07:00,147
Can we please change
the subject?

164
00:07:00,149 --> 00:07:02,716
O-Okay.

165
00:07:02,718 --> 00:07:06,053
How 'bout we change it to why
you're being weird about this?

166
00:07:06,055 --> 00:07:07,154
I'm not being weird.

167
00:07:07,156 --> 00:07:09,390
I...

168
00:07:09,392 --> 00:07:11,392
It's hard to explain.

169
00:07:11,394 --> 00:07:15,296
Sheldon, just tell me.

170
00:07:16,165 --> 00:07:18,198
It might be easier to show you.

171
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:20,367
Okay.

172
00:07:21,237 --> 00:07:23,804
We'd have to take your car.

173
00:07:23,806 --> 00:07:25,973
All right.

174
00:07:28,344 --> 00:07:31,979
And I'm gonna need you to sign
a nondisclosure agreement.

175
00:07:32,949 --> 00:07:36,317
Well, I signed one
before we slept together.

176
00:07:36,319 --> 00:07:38,485
Why not now?

177
00:07:42,525 --> 00:07:45,392
Penny says they're having fun
working on the prototype.

178
00:07:45,394 --> 00:07:49,063
Remember when her fun was
nightclubs and drinking games?

179
00:07:49,065 --> 00:07:51,699
I know. I'm lowering
the bar so slowly.

180
00:07:51,701 --> 00:07:54,835
This time next year
she'll have a coin collection.

181
00:07:54,837 --> 00:07:56,236
Excuse me.

182
00:07:56,238 --> 00:07:58,505
You guys interested in a free
screening of an upcoming movie?

183
00:07:58,507 --> 00:07:59,406
Oh. Sorry, we can't.

184
00:07:59,408 --> 00:08:01,375
Well, hang on.
What movie is it?

185
00:08:01,377 --> 00:08:04,178
Oh, I can't tell you.
But it does star Will Smith.

186
00:08:04,180 --> 00:08:06,046
Wait.

187
00:08:06,048 --> 00:08:07,481
I bet it's <i>Suicide Squad.</i>

188
00:08:07,483 --> 00:08:09,283
Let's check it out.

189
00:08:09,285 --> 00:08:10,484
What about the girls?

190
00:08:10,486 --> 00:08:12,286
Penny just said
they're having fun.

191
00:08:12,288 --> 00:08:14,822
Honestly, you want to wrap tape
around a bunch of pipe fittings

192
00:08:14,824 --> 00:08:16,290
all afternoon?

193
00:08:17,259 --> 00:08:18,492
Okay, we'll take 'em.

194
00:08:18,494 --> 00:08:20,327
Okay.
But, I swear,

195
00:08:20,329 --> 00:08:22,329
if it's Will Smith
in <i>Shark Tale 2,</i>

196
00:08:22,331 --> 00:08:25,699
it better be at least as good
as the original.

197
00:08:26,936 --> 00:08:28,602
I mean, it's crazy,
isn't it?

198
00:08:28,604 --> 00:08:30,738
I moved here from Nebraska
to be an actress,

199
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:33,707
and now I'm sitting
in an engineering lab at Caltech

200
00:08:33,709 --> 00:08:37,911
helping to build a prototype
for a high-tech guidance system.

201
00:08:37,913 --> 00:08:39,913
It is crazy. It's also crazy

202
00:08:39,915 --> 00:08:43,417
that I've made 14 of these
and you've made three.

203
00:08:43,419 --> 00:08:45,452
(knocking)

204
00:08:46,355 --> 00:08:48,822
Hey. Where are the guys?

205
00:08:48,824 --> 00:08:50,224
Oh, they went to the store
to get solder,

206
00:08:50,226 --> 00:08:53,827
which is metal you melt
to make science things.

207
00:08:54,730 --> 00:08:56,330
Since when
do you work on weekends?

208
00:08:56,332 --> 00:08:57,831
I'm an astrophysicist.

209
00:08:57,833 --> 00:09:00,100
The stars don't take a day off.

210
00:09:00,102 --> 00:09:02,903
You were home alone
and had no one to play with?

211
00:09:02,905 --> 00:09:06,173
Well, the cleaning lady was
there, but she doesn't like me.

212
00:09:07,343 --> 00:09:08,709
You need any help?

213
00:09:08,711 --> 00:09:11,345
Not with
Lightning McQueen here.

214
00:09:11,347 --> 00:09:13,080
I think we're good.

215
00:09:13,082 --> 00:09:14,648
Okay. That's cool.

216
00:09:14,650 --> 00:09:16,984
I guess everybody's involved
in this project but me.

217
00:09:16,986 --> 00:09:19,753
So... see ya.

218
00:09:19,755 --> 00:09:22,423
(door shuts)

219
00:09:22,425 --> 00:09:23,457
I feel bad.

220
00:09:23,459 --> 00:09:24,525
Should we have asked him
to stay?

221
00:09:24,527 --> 00:09:26,694
KOOTHRAPPALI (high-pitched):
Yes.

222
00:09:29,865 --> 00:09:32,266
Will you please tell me
where we're going?

223
00:09:32,268 --> 00:09:35,936
Sorry, you're on
a need-to-know basis.

224
00:09:36,872 --> 00:09:38,172
I'm driving the car.

225
00:09:38,174 --> 00:09:40,541
I need to know.

226
00:09:40,543 --> 00:09:41,608
Right.

227
00:09:41,610 --> 00:09:43,310
So where are we going?

228
00:09:43,312 --> 00:09:46,814
No, I meant turn right,
and you missed it.

229
00:09:46,816 --> 00:09:49,483
Maybe you do need to know.

230
00:09:51,787 --> 00:09:53,821
(indistinct chatter)

231
00:09:53,823 --> 00:09:55,022
What are we gonna tell
the girls?

232
00:09:55,024 --> 00:09:56,190
It's not a problem.

233
00:09:56,192 --> 00:09:57,324
I mean without lying.

234
00:09:57,326 --> 00:09:59,693
And now you've made it
a problem.

235
00:09:59,695 --> 00:10:01,762
Come on. We're
a couple of smart guys.

236
00:10:01,764 --> 00:10:03,630
I'm sure we can come up
with a way to explain this

237
00:10:03,632 --> 00:10:05,299
that doesn't make us
look bad.

238
00:10:05,301 --> 00:10:07,167
(phone chimes)

239
00:10:07,169 --> 00:10:09,103
Oh!

240
00:10:09,105 --> 00:10:10,904
The boys had to drive
all the way to San Bernardino

241
00:10:10,906 --> 00:10:12,740
for the solder and got a flat.

242
00:10:14,810 --> 00:10:15,843
(phone chimes)

243
00:10:15,845 --> 00:10:18,245
They bought it.

244
00:10:18,247 --> 00:10:19,813
But we're gonna have to

245
00:10:19,815 --> 00:10:21,448
put the spare on
before we go back.

246
00:10:21,450 --> 00:10:23,150
Oh, you're good at this.

247
00:10:23,152 --> 00:10:25,486
Well, I lie a lot.

248
00:10:26,322 --> 00:10:27,988
MAN:
Hey, guys, thank you

249
00:10:27,990 --> 00:10:29,923
for being a part of our
test screening. You're about

250
00:10:29,925 --> 00:10:32,626
to be one of the first audiences
to see <i>Suicide Squad.</i>

251
00:10:32,628 --> 00:10:34,595
(applause and cheering)
Hey!

252
00:10:34,597 --> 00:10:35,863
(laughs)
You were right.

253
00:10:35,865 --> 00:10:36,997
Oh, I keep telling you--

254
00:10:36,999 --> 00:10:40,534
good things happen
to bad people.

255
00:10:40,536 --> 00:10:42,569
Uh, we're gonna get started
in a couple minutes. Enjoy.

256
